<br>
Her sea blue occulars, lit up by the flame of the candles next to her, gazed along the crowd, staring at each individual which stood still and silenced as Ardyn spoke.  As she moved her head, her long braid of black and white locks wrapped by a long black sting of leather which started at the beginning and was wrapped all the way down to the end of the braid moved from her shoulder and onto her back.<br>
<br>
When her niece handed her the mask, she took it greatfully.  With that she stood to her feet as all the amazons demanded a speech from her.  Once she was on her feet, she took one step closer to the edge of the platform which they stood.  She took one more unsure look along the crowd before bringing her hand up to silence them.<br>
<br>
A loud cheer rolled through the crowd as the hand meant that she was about to make one.  As they cheered a smile fell across her face as her maternal instinct kicked in and influenced her about what to make the speech on.<br>
<br>
&quot;My athelfi, my moro!  It brings me great joy to be Vasillissa of your tribe!  As a mother does for her young, I shall nurture, I shall care, I shall raise you and your children!  My athelfi, to me, you are my children, and I shall love you as much as I love my own!<br>
<br>
Now, I may not rule like your old Queen, Ardyn, and that is because no one can!  Ardyn-Tyger is a great ruler and that is why she must go and tend to our O'the Wind Clan!  She must bring what triumph she brought to you over to them!  Do no fret, for I am sure she will visit this tribe, if not I will have to go and drag her back here!  For she may depart to her clan, but in her heart she will never leave this land.  For once an amazon, always an amazon!&quot;<br>
<br>
The crowd cheered at her words, another loud roar exploded from the crowd as she turned towards her little niece for more instructions. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center">eygra O'the W¡nd<br>
